               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540227-name-22" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-22" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-22" type="surname" value="EDGILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-22" type="given" value="RICHARD HENRY"></interp>RICHARD HENRY EDGILL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to F. W. Rolland and Co., of Union-court, Old Broad-street. On 11th Feb., about a quarter past 10 o'clock, I was passing over London-bridge, and felt a <hi rend="italic">tug</hi> at my right pocket—I stopped, and saw the prisoner at my right side with my handkerchief in his right hand—I seized him, and held him till a policeman came—he asked me to let him go, and said he would not do it again, and so forth—I cannot accurately say what it was, or whether he said, "again."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540227-name-23" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-23" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-23" type="surname" value="CHESTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-23" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CHESTER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>). I was on duty, on London-bridge, about a quarter past 10 o'clock—there was an obstruction, and I saw Mr. Edgill holding the prisoner—I went up, and he said the prisoner had picked his pocket—I asked him if he intended to give him into custody; he said, "Yes" the prisoner said, "I did not take the handkerchief; some other person took it, and gave it to me."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540227-name-24" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-24" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-24" type="surname" value="EDGILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540227-name-24" type="given" value="RICHARD HENRY"></interp>RICHARD HENRY EDGILL</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> There was a gentleman passing, who ran for a policeman, but the prisoner was directly at my side when I turned round—I saw no other person running away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> A lad passed by me, and gave the handkerchief into my hand; I stopped and looked, and the gentleman asked me for it; I gave it to him.</p>
